Thandi SetokoeAt the back from left are, Duwayne Putter and Loyiso Mafele from the Come Learn Educational, Youth and Community Development Centre, with the Jack family members Nyaniswa and Sinesipho, and Anelisa, Sibusiso, Linathi and Sive all in front. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories A WALMER Township family recently lost everything when their shack burnt down. The Come Learn Educatio-nal, Youth and Community Development Centre assisted the Jack family in rebuilding their lives by providing a new wardrobe of clothes for eight family members as well as blankets and food. The organisation is also providing the family with emotional support with follow-up visits and spiritual care.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.